				\begin{document}$d\overline{S}/dr$\end{document}, is negative but nearly adiabatic due to the efficient mixing of entropy by turbulent convection. The convective enthalpy flux is positive (outward) and the radiative heat flux normalized by the total flux, L⊙/4πr2 is less than unity. To a good approximation, the normalized convective enthalpy flux and radiative heat flux sum to unity, with smaller contributions from the other terms in Equation (3).
